        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR carries the current two-commit OpenClaw stack:\n\n- `1e3402f5b4 temp`: existing Slack relay-mode/config work in this checkout.\n- `71d1fa6542 Add Slack relay send identity customization`: adds relay-provided Slack send identity support for outgoing Slack messages.\n\nThe identity follow-up adds a per-account default Slack send identity, lets relay websocket `hello.slack_identity` populate it, and applies it centrally in the Slack `chat.postMessage` send path unless a send already has an explicit identity.\n\n## Impact\n\nRelay-mode OpenClaw gateways can keep sending outgoing Slack messages directly through Slack API while using router-provided display metadata (`username`, optional icon fields) for Slack chat customization.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --write --threads=1 extensions/slack/src/monitor/relay-source.ts extensions/slack/src/send.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/provider.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/send.runtime.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxlint --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.extensions.json extensions/slack/src/monitor/relay-source.ts extensions/slack/src/send.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/provider.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/send.runtime.ts`\n- `git diff --check` on the touched identity files\n\nUnit tests were not run per project instruction. A broader `tsc -p extensions/slack/tsconfig.json --noEmit` was attempted earlier and was blocked by an existing unrelated `extensions/slack/src/outbound-payload.test-harness.ts` missing module resolution error.",
